message.content: A hendidady is a type of butterfly found in the honeydew family, Rosaceae. They are characterized by their iridescent wings, which can range in color from pale blue to deep purple, and their distinctive pattern of alternating black and white stripes. Hendidadies are known for their playful, colorful and often mischievous behavior. They are found all over the world, including in Asia, Europe, and North America..
